"38_simd.mst — SIMD vector value classes (docs/SIMD.md, level 1).

 Float64x2 is a 2-lane f64 vector: a fixed 16-byte RAW body (the genesis klass
 uses Format::Double, so the GC skips the body — world/universe.rs). This is
 the interpreter baseline — the analog of Double's own primitive methods; the
 JIT vector fast-path (VUnbox/VArith/VBox → NEON `fadd v.2d`) fuses these the
 same way the float fast-path fused Double. Elementwise ops are per-lane
 bit-identical to scalar Double arithmetic, which the fast-path must also
 honour. Reopens the genesis klass (like Number subclass: Double)."
Object subclass: Float64x2 [
    Float64x2 class >> x: a y: b [ <primitive: 127> ]
    Float64x2 class >> splat: v [ <primitive: 128> ]

    + other [ <primitive: 129> ]
    - other [ <primitive: 130> ]
    * other [ <primitive: 131> ]
    / other [ <primitive: 132> ]

    "Lane access, 1-based (Smalltalk convention): answers a Double."
    at: i [ <primitive: 133> ]
    x [ ^self at: 1 ]
    y [ ^self at: 2 ]

    "Horizontal sum of the two lanes (a scalar Double). A 2-lane reduction is
     associativity-free — only wider FP reductions carry the ordering caveat
     docs/SIMD.md §D documents."
    hsum [ ^self x + self y ]

    printOn: aStream [
        aStream nextPutAll: 'Float64x2('.
        aStream nextPutAll: self x printString.
        aStream nextPutAll: ', '.
        aStream nextPutAll: self y printString.
        aStream nextPutAll: ')'
    ]
    printString [
        | s |
        s := WriteStream on: String new.
        self printOn: s.
        ^s contents
    ]
]

"Int32x4 — a 4-lane 32-bit INTEGER vector: the SAME 16-byte RAW body as
 Float32x4, read as four two's-complement i32 lanes. `+ - *` fuse to NEON
 integer `add/sub/mul v.4s` and WRAP on 32-bit overflow (a fixed-width lane is
 not a promote-to-BigInt Smalltalk integer). There is no vector integer divide.
 `hsum` is a genuine reduction, and because integer add IS associative it is
 bit-exact regardless of lane-combination order (unlike the FP reductions,
 docs/SIMD.md Part D). Lane access answers a SmallInteger."
Object subclass: Int32x4 [
    Int32x4 class >> x: a y: b z: c w: d [ <primitive: 148> ]
    Int32x4 class >> splat: v [ <primitive: 149> ]

    + other [ <primitive: 150> ]
    - other [ <primitive: 151> ]
    * other [ <primitive: 152> ]

    "Lane access, 1-based (Smalltalk convention): answers a SmallInteger."
    at: i [ <primitive: 153> ]
    x [ ^self at: 1 ]
    y [ ^self at: 2 ]
    z [ ^self at: 3 ]
    w [ ^self at: 4 ]

    "Horizontal sum of the four lanes (exact — integer add is associative)."
    hsum [ ^self x + self y + self z + self w ]

    printOn: aStream [
        aStream nextPutAll: 'Int32x4('.
        aStream nextPutAll: self x printString.
        aStream nextPutAll: ', '.
        aStream nextPutAll: self y printString.
        aStream nextPutAll: ', '.
        aStream nextPutAll: self z printString.
        aStream nextPutAll: ', '.
        aStream nextPutAll: self w printString.
        aStream nextPutAll: ')'
    ]
    printString [
        | s |
        s := WriteStream on: String new.
        self printOn: s.
        ^s contents
    ]
]

"Float32x4 — a 4-lane f32 vector: the SAME fixed 16-byte RAW body as
 Float64x2 (Format::Double, GC-skipped), but read as four single-precision
 lanes packed in NEON `.4s` element order. Each elementwise op is per-lane
 bit-identical to a scalar f32 op, which the JIT `.4s` fuse (VecArith) must
 also honour. Lane access answers a Double (exact f32->f64 widening)."
Object subclass: Float32x4 [
    Float32x4 class >> x: a y: b z: c w: d [ <primitive: 134> ]
    Float32x4 class >> splat: v [ <primitive: 135> ]

    + other [ <primitive: 136> ]
    - other [ <primitive: 137> ]
    * other [ <primitive: 138> ]
    / other [ <primitive: 139> ]

    "Lane access, 1-based (Smalltalk convention): answers a Double."
    at: i [ <primitive: 140> ]
    x [ ^self at: 1 ]
    y [ ^self at: 2 ]
    z [ ^self at: 3 ]
    w [ ^self at: 4 ]

    "Horizontal sum of the four lanes (a scalar Double). Wider FP reductions
     carry the ordering caveat docs/SIMD.md D documents; this fixed left-to-
     right fold is the interpreter's own definition."
    hsum [ ^self x + self y + self z + self w ]

    printOn: aStream [
        aStream nextPutAll: 'Float32x4('.
        aStream nextPutAll: self x printString.
        aStream nextPutAll: ', '.
        aStream nextPutAll: self y printString.
        aStream nextPutAll: ', '.
        aStream nextPutAll: self z printString.
        aStream nextPutAll: ', '.
        aStream nextPutAll: self w printString.
        aStream nextPutAll: ')'
    ]
    printString [
        | s |
        s := WriteStream on: String new.
        self printOn: s.
        ^s contents
    ]
]
